remarks.format:
  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="addd1-102">音声の正規化とは、特殊な構成要素または記号を使用して音声の書き込みを表現することです。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-102">Speech normalization is the use of special constructs or symbols to express speech in writing.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="addd1-103">たとえば、次のようなテキストが認識されているとします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-103">For example, suppose that this is recognized text:</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="addd1-104">"12 31 年7月4日午後に、14ドルと6セントの魚を1か所に購入しました。これは、シアトルワシントン 9 8 1 2 2 州シアトルのシャーマンの場で市場に出回っています"</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-104">"july four at twelve thirty one PM, I bought one point six kilograms of fish for fourteen dollars and six cents, at the pike place market in seattle washington nine eight one two two"</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="addd1-105">これは、正規化後のテキストと同じです。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-105">This is the same text after normalization:</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="addd1-106">"12:31 年7月4日に、シアトル WA 98122 のシャーマンプレース市場で $14.06 の 1.6 kg を購入しました。"</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-106">"July 4 at 12:31 PM, I bought 1.6 kg of fish for $14.06, at the pike place market in Seattle WA 98122"</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="addd1-107">この例では、5つの置換があり、それぞれのインスタンス<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>によって記述されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-107">In this example there are five substitutions, each of which would be described by an instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="addd1-108">アプリケーションでは、オブジェクトを使用して次のことを決定できます。 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText></span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-108">Using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> object, an application can determine:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="addd1-109">正規化によって置き換えられた単語の場所と数。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-109">The location and number of words replaced by normalization.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="addd1-110">詳細については、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.CountOfWords%2A><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.FirstWordIndex%2A>」または」を参照してください。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-110">For more information, see <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.FirstWordIndex%2A> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.CountOfWords%2A>.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="addd1-111">置換されたテキストとその表示属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-111">The replaced text and its display attributes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="addd1-112">詳細については<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.Text%2A>、「 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.DisplayAttributes%2A>」および「」を参照してください。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-112">For more information, see <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.Text%2A>, and  <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText.DisplayAttributes%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="addd1-113"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>のインスタンスは、通常はの<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.ReplacementWordUnits%2A>プロパティに<xref:System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection%601>よって返されるオブジェクトのメンバーとして取得さ<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>れます ( <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>または、返されたテキストがの場合は、から継承されるクラス)。正規化.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-113">Instances of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> are typically obtained as members of the <xref:System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection%601> object returned by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.ReplacementWordUnits%2A> property on <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> (or classes that inherit from <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>, such as <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>) when returned text has been normalized.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="addd1-114">次の例では、認識エンジンによって<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>返されるオブジェクトに関するユーザーインターフェイスの情報を表示します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="addd1-114">The example below displays information in a user interface about a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> object returned by a recognition engine.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
internal static void DisplayBasicPhraseInfo(  
        Label label,   
        RecognizedPhrase result,   
        SpeechRecognizer rec)   
{  
  if (result != null && label != null)   
  {  
    // Blank  
    if (rec != null)   
    {   
      // Clear  
      label.Text += String.Format(  
                             "  Recognizer currently at:   {0} mSec\n" +  
                             "  Audio Device currently at: {1} mSec\n",  
                             rec.RecognizerAudioPosition.TotalMilliseconds,  
                             rec.AudioPosition.TotalMilliseconds);  
    }  
  
    if (result != null)   
    { // Clear  
      RecognitionResult recResult = result as RecognitionResult;  
      if (recResult != null)   
      {  
        RecognizedAudio resultAudio = recResult.Audio;  
        if (resultAudio == null)   
        {  
          label.Text += String.Format("  Emulated input\n");  
        }   
        else   
        {  
          label.Text += String.Format(  
                               "  Candidate Phrase at:       {0} mSec\n" +  
                               "  Phrase Length:             {1} mSec\n" +  
                               "  Input State Time:          {2}\n" +  
                               "  Input Format:              {3}\n",  
                               resultAudio.AudioPosition.TotalMilliseconds,  
                               resultAudio.Duration.TotalMilliseconds,  
                               resultAudio.StartTime.ToShortTimeString(),  
                               resultAudio.Format.EncodingFormat.ToString());  
        }  
      }  
  
      label.Text += String.Format("  Confidence Level:          {0}\n", result.Confidence);  
      if (result.Grammar != null)   
      {  
        label.Text += String.Format(  
                            "  Recognizing Grammar:       {0}\n" +  
                            "  Recognizing Rule:          {1}\n",  
                            ((result.Grammar.Name != null) ? (result.Grammar.Name) : "None"),  
                            ((result.Grammar.RuleName != null) ? (result.Grammar.RuleName) : "None"));  
      }  
  
      if  (result.ReplacementWordUnits.Count !=  0)    
      {  
        label.Text += String.Format("  Replacement text:\n");  
        foreach (ReplacementText rep in result.ReplacementWordUnits)    
        {  
          string repText = rep.Text;  
          // Add trailing spaces  
  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.OneTrailingSpace) !=  0)    
          {  
            repText += " ";  
          }  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.TwoTrailingSpaces) !=  0)    
          {  
            repText += "  ";  
          }  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.ConsumeLeadingSpaces) != 0)    
          {  
            repText=repText.TrimStart();  
          }  
          if ((rep.DisplayAttributes & DisplayAttributes.ZeroTrailingSpaces) != 0)   
          {  
            repText = repText.TrimEnd();  
          }  
          label.Text += String.Format(  
                           "      At index {0} for {1} words. Text: \"{2}\"\n",  
                           rep.FirstWordIndex,  rep.CountOfWords, repText);  
  
        }  
        label.Text += String.Format("\n\n");  
      }  
    }  
  }    
}  
```

  
  
